column5: I think I've eaten more than that at Thanksgiving.  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aNYG0JD7Ot8
For some reason, I've got some reservations about going down a river with pointy rocks.
Dacron is pretty tough, hang-gliders are covered in it.
Now that is a canoe I wouldn't mind portaging for a change! It looks like it would be fun to play around in too, turns on a dime.

Interesting and have seen other builds that use beefier ribs and planks.  I will say though that seeing people switch sides every stroke drives me crazy ! Learn proper strokes and pick a side. Every paddler should know j's, pries and draws. ok, I feel better...

"I will say though that seeing people switch sides every stroke drives me crazy ! Learn proper strokes and pick a side. Every paddler should know j's, pries and draws. ok, I feel better..."  Hehe! Too funny...I thought the same. Seems strange to go through all the trouble of building your own craft but don't know how to properly paddle it!
best thing paddlers can do is take a whitewater course and learn river reading and paddle skills, skills which do translate into flat water paddling.
